<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.ExtraExtraLarge" Style="@($"background:{Colors.Shades.White};height:100%")">
    <MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Large" Class="py-5">
        <img src="./logo-vertical-black-description.svg" Style="height:200px;display:inline-block;float:left;padding-right:1rem;padding-bottom:1rem;" /> <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">eHulog is a startup that hopes and believes that  every person has a kind heart. A burning desire to come together, do good and affect change even in the smallest of things.</MudText>
        <br />
        <br />
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">
            The providers of this social community are called lenders. These unsung heroes with resources they are willing to share and give to others in need
        </MudText>
        <br />
        <br />
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Lessees are those in need who for one reason or another would like to endure, smile and still be a good part of the social fabric. eHulog connects lenders with lessees for their emergencies and dire situations. eHulog makes it easier for them to find those good providers.</MudText>
        <br />
        <br />
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">eHulog is bridging and bringing together the haves and have-nots in a more subtle and secure way without having to go through tedious process of queueing, waiting for your applications for days, proving financial capacities and background evaluations.</MudText>
        <br />
        <br />
        <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">
            eHulog's mission is to provide a harmonious place where service providers are happy to make a positive impact on those in need, and the person in need continues to be a functioning member of the community without worrying about where to turn for difficult needs and emergencies.
        </MudText>
    </MudContainer>

